<h1>Problem 1159 - 2002 IMO, P2 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>The circle \(S\) has centre \(O\), and \(BC\) is a diameter of \(S\). Let \(A\) be a point of \(S\) such that \(\angle AOB<120{{}^\circ}\). Let \(D\) be the midpoint of the arc \(AB\) which does not contain \(C\). The line through \(O\) parallel to \(DA\) meets the line \(AC\) at \(I\). The perpendicular bisector of \(OA\) meets \(S\) at \(E\) and at \(F\). Prove that \(I\) is the incentre of the triangle \(CEF.\)</p>
